originalText.text: I recently worked with Christian at Movage to manage a cross country move from New York to Colorado. Christian was on top of it and responsive the whole way. Costs we're clear and up front. The movers did a fantastic job of protecting, labeling, and moving my furniture and boxes. Everything arrived quickly and without incident. Thanks Christian!

I canâ€™t believe I have to write this review, but I figured it was fair to warn everyone whoâ€™s looking to use Movage for a long distance move. (We moved from NJ to CA.) (tldr: lack of communication, damaged boxes and furniture upon arrival, poor quality of service)

In the beginning, Jeff was very attentive and made us feel like â€œYes! This is the quality of service weâ€™re looking for in a company!â€ and the quoted price was great. He told us everything we needed to know about our move and we were excited to move forward. (Disclaimer: Low price is because they have other moves on the same truck as yours. We figured it wouldnâ€™t be a problem... it was.) But once we had our stuff loaded on to the truck, thatâ€™s when it went all downhill.

First things first, the pick-up movers told us how much we should be tipping them (they said they wanted 20%), which was extremely unprofessional. I donâ€™t mind if they had just mentioned that tips are appreciated, but to have the balls to flat out tell me you want 20%? Really?

I didnâ€™t hear from Jeff for about a week after our initial pick-up, and when he did respond, all he could tell me was that our stuff was still waiting to be put onto the truck and our 6 day delivery window remained the same. He told me he would update with information when he had some. I asked him if it was possible to get a tighter delivery window once the truck was in transit and he informed me that once we got closer to the delivery window heâ€™d have a better estimate of when our stuff should be arriving. (At this point, we were 9 days from the first day of our delivery window and 7 days since pick-up.)

Another we goes by without any correspondence from Jeff. Iâ€™m starting to get a little anxious because itâ€™s 2 days from the first day of our delivery window and we have no idea where our stuff is. So I contact him again asking if he had an update. The first day of the delivery window is pushed back a day. Still very vague. I ask again if he could provided a tighter delivery window since were working people and need to make arrangements to receive this move if it does come on a work day. He said heâ€™ll try his best.

So now itâ€™s the first day of the delivery window! Hurray! But silence on Jeffâ€™s end. At this point, we figured heâ€™d have some sort of idea where the truck is and have an idea of when the truck should be arriving to us. I email Jeff and no response. I get that itâ€™s a Saturday, but if client is paying thousands of dollars to use your services, just a quick acknowledgement would be appreciated.

We get a call later that day from the driver saying heâ€™s in the area and will delivery the following day or the next, depending on the other deliveries. Okay, great! But why wasnâ€™t Jeff able to provide that information to us? The driver told us that theyâ€™re not actually a part of Movage and theyâ€™re hired to do jobs within Movage (which was one of the first questions I asked because I wanted to make sure that the move wasnâ€™t being contracted out to third parties ðŸ˜’), so the drivers themselves werenâ€™t even in touch with Movage at all.

And then our stuff finally arrives... boxes were damaged, wet, opened, our couch was soaked on one side... Iâ€™ll let the pictures do the talking.

The response we get after we express our extreme disappointment is just a very textbook: â€œI apologize for any inconvenience. This is not the typical feed back we receive from our customers. I will help you as much as possible as I have tried to do from the first time we spoke. I will attach a claims form to this email. Please fill it out at your earliest convenience so we can start a claim process for you. Thank you.â€

If youâ€™re looking to do a long distance move, go with Mayflower. We deeply regret not choosing to go with them in the first place.

originalText.text: I had a great experience with Movage. The team was punctual, and polite, and worked quickly to get everything packed and loaded onto the truck. They were also very communicative throughout the entire process, which made me feel at ease. I would definitely hire them again.

originalText.text:
Recently we move household goods from Switzerland to the Seattle. Fortunately, the firm we contacted in Switzerland worked in conjunction with Movage Moving+Storage. The move went seamless with no problems, no breakage and everything happen as promised. The drivers when arriving in Seattle were very professional and friendly.
I would use them again in the future and recommend them for any move.

originalText.text:
Movage was excellent! They helped us with our move from NYC > Alexandria, VA. Christian was our coordinator and was fantastic from first contact, getting a quote, and preparing us for what would happen on the day. He answered all my (many) questions. Enrique & the crew were efficient, thoughtful, and detailed oriented. Great communication from start to finish. All of our things were as we had packed them - no damage, or even any noticeable wear & tear on the boxes from the move.

Their binding price - which is for real! - and was very reasonable. We worked with Christian to get the quote and then there were no unexpected surprises.

Again, would recommend Movage 100% - easy to work with, great staff & crew, and they take care in their work!
